  <prompt>
    Build `WizardAttachmentSource.tsx` at `subcomponents/sources/WizardAttachmentSource.tsx`. Renders files uploaded earlier in the parent wizard (e.g., DocumentEmailWizard, SummarizeFilesWizard) and lets the user select which to attach.

    Behavior:
    - Receives `wizardContext: { uploadedFiles: Array<{ documentId: string; driveItemId: string; name: string; sizeBytes: number; mimeType?: string }> }` from props (engine forwards from host)
    - Per UQ5 resolution: `wizardContext.uploadedFiles` shape includes BOTH `documentId` AND `driveItemId`. Composer uses `driveItemId` as the canonical attachment reference (NOT documentId).
    - Renders a Dialog or inline list of uploaded files with checkboxes
    - On confirm, produces `IAttachment[]` with `source='wizard'`, `driveItemId: file.driveItemId`, `name`, `sizeBytes`, `mimeType`

    If `wizardContext.uploadedFiles` is empty or undefined, the picker button is disabled with a hint "No files uploaded in this wizard yet".
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer comfortable with the shared lib's wizardContext conventions.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `WizardAttachmentSource.tsx` compiles + lint-clean. Picker lists wizardContext.uploadedFiles; selected entries add to AttachmentList with `driveItemId` correctly populated (NOT documentId).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per UQ5 resolution + FR-07: wizardContext is the existing convention in shared lib wizards (DocumentEmailWizard, SummarizeFilesWizard pass it to their send-email step). The shape includes `documentId` (Dataverse `sprk_document` GUID) AND `driveItemId` (SPE driveItem ID).

      EmailComposer always uses `driveItemId` â€” this consistency closes the FR-17 / DocumentEmailWizard:494 latent bug class at the engine level.

      Audit existing wizardContext shape in `DocumentEmailWizard.tsx` and `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` to confirm the field names match. If the existing shape differs, document the delta and adapt.
    </background>
